# UI Patterns

Reuse the shared component stack below. Do not invent ad-hoc tables, search, or layout patterns.

## Page Layout

- Wrap feature views in `PageShell` (`title`, `description`, optional `actions` for primary CTA).
- Nest list content in `Card` → `CardHeader` / `CardContent`.
- Reference: `WorkOrderListView`, `LeaseListView`.

## Data Tables (Standard List Pattern)

Use `DataTable` from `@/components/shared/DataTable` with `FULL_TABLE` from `@/lib/data-table/full-table`:

```tsx
import { FULL_TABLE, fullTableSort } from "@/lib/data-table/full-table";

<DataTable
  {...FULL_TABLE}
  data={rows}
  searchPlaceholder="Search …"
  searchKeys={["id", "title", "unitLabel"]}
  defaultSort={fullTableSort("createdAt", "desc")}
  columns={[
    { key: "title", header: "Title", sortable: true, cell: (row) => row.title },
  ]}
/>
```

- `FULL_TABLE` enables: `searchable`, `sortable`, `paginated`, `filterable`, `defaultPageSize: 10`.
- Columns: `key`, `header`, `cell`, plus optional `sortable`, `sortValue`, `filterable`, `filterKey`.
- Row menus: `actions` prop → `RowActions` dropdown. Do not build per-row button clusters.
- Filters: `DataTableFilterSheet` opens automatically when `filterable` is on.
- Use `ComboboxField` for filter/form fields with 5+ options.
- Do not roll custom search/sort/pagination — `useDataTable` is wired inside `DataTable`.

## Display Helpers

- `StatusBadge` — workflow states in table cells
- `CurrencyDisplay` — monetary values
- `DatePickerField` — date inputs in forms

## Forms & Destructive Actions

- Create/edit: `FormSheet` + `FormGrid` / `FormField`
- Destructive actions: `ConfirmDialog` before calling the service

## Dashboards

- `PageShell` → `DashboardWidget` KPI grid → optional `DataTable` with `{...FULL_TABLE}`

## Global Search

- `GlobalCommandMenu` is for **page navigation** (Cmd+K), not in-page data search.
- In-page data search belongs on `DataTable`.

## Anti-Patterns

- Raw shadcn `Table` for interactive list views
- Custom filter/search state when `DataTable` + `FULL_TABLE` covers the use case
- Marketing-style hero layouts or non-productivity UI
